TYPE: Test,
TARGET: power supply module output and first control module input cabling,
DESCRIPTION: With a known-good 12 V battery now installed, use a multimeter to verify that ~12 V is present across the two output cables of the power supply module. Then, while keeping battery connected, measure voltage at the input pair of cables on Control Module 1 (on the face connected to the PSU). Compare: if 12 V is at the PSU outputs but not at Control Module 1 inputs, suspect a mis-connection or swapped cables between PSU and Control Module 1; if no 12 V at PSU outputs, suspect an internal open or miswired connection in the power supply module itself.,
RESULT: 12 V is present between PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−), and the same ~12 V is present between Control Input Cable (+) 1 and Control Input Cable (−) 1. No polarity inversion is detected between the PSU output cables and Control Module 1 input cables.
